value.value: The membrane surrounding the inner segment of a vertebrate photoreceptor. The photoreceptor inner segment contains mitochondria, ribosomes and membranes where opsin molecules are assembled and passed to be part of the outer segment discs.

The process of creating a trabecula in an organ. A trabecula is a small, often microscopic, tissue element in the form of a small beam, strut or rod, which generally has a mechanical function. Trabecula are usually but not necessarily, composed of dense collagenous tissue.
The process of creating a trabecula in the liver. A trabecula is a tissue element in the form of a small beam, strut or rod.
The process of creating a trabecula in the spleen. A trabecula is a tissue element in the form of a small beam, strut or rod.
The process of creating a trabecula in the bone. A trabecula is a tissue element in the form of a small beam, strut or rod.
The process of creating a trabecula in the heart. A trabecula is a tissue element in the form of a small beam, strut or rod.

The process whose specific outcome is the progression of bone over time, from its formation to the mature structure. Bone is the hard skeletal connective tissue consisting of both mineral and cellular components.
The process in which bones are generated and organized.
The process in which bones are generated and organized as a result of the conversion of initial cartilaginous anlage into bone.

label.value: cartilage development involved in endochondral bone morphogenesis

value.value: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of the cartilage that will provide a scaffold for mineralization of endochondral bones.
The appearance of a cell adhesion molecule due to biosynthesis or secretion.

label.value: regulation of cell adhesion molecule production

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of cell adhesion molecule production. Cell adhesion molecule production is the appearance of a cell adhesion molecule as a result of its biosynthesis or a decrease in its catabolism.

label.value: negative regulation of cell adhesion molecule production

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of cell adhesion molecule production. Cell adhesion molecule production is the appearance of a cell adhesion molecule as a result of its biosynthesis or a decrease in its catabolism.

label.value: positive regulation of cell adhesion molecule production

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of cell adhesion molecule production. Cell adhesion molecule production is the appearance of a cell adhesion molecule as a result of its biosynthesis or a decrease in its catabolism.
Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of an ammonium stimulus.

label.value: negative regulation of leucine import in response to ammonium ion

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of leucine import as a result of an ammonium ion stimulus. Leucine import is the directed movement of leucine into a cell or organelle.
Self-propelled movement of an organism from one location to another through the air, usually by means of active wing movement.
Self-propelled movement of an organism from one location to another through the air that is part of the organism's response to external or internal stimuli resulting in flight.
The process in which any suture between cranial bones is generated and organized.
The process in which the frontal suture is generated and organized.
The process in which the coronal suture is generated and organized.
The process in which the lambdoid suture is generated and organized.
The process in which the sagittal suture is generated and organized.

label.value: regulation of Fc receptor mediated stimulatory signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of the Fc receptor mediated stimulatory signaling pathway..

label.value: positive regulation of Fc receptor mediated stimulatory signaling pathway

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of the Fc receptor mediated stimulatory signaling pathway.

label.value: susceptibility to T cell mediated cytotoxicity

value.value: The process of causing a cell to become susceptible to T cell mediated cytotoxicity.

label.value: regulation of atrial cardiac muscle cell membrane depolarization

value.value: Any process that modulates the establishment or extent of a membrane potential in the depolarizing direction away from the resting potential in an atrial cardiomyocyte.

label.value: regulation of atrial cardiac muscle cell membrane repolarization

value.value: Any process that modulates the establishment or extent of a membrane potential in the polarizing direction towards the resting potential in an atrial cardiomyocyte.

label.value: regulation of ventricular cardiac muscle cell membrane depolarization

value.value: Any process that modulates the establishment or extent of a membrane potential in the depolarizing direction away from the resting potential in a ventricular cardiomyocyte.

The process in which a relatively unspecialized myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a mast cell. A mast cell is a cell that is found in almost all tissues containing numerous basophilic granules and capable of releasing large amounts of histamine and heparin upon activation.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of mast cell differentiation, the process in which a relatively unspecialized myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a mast cell. A mast cell is a cell that is found in almost all tissues containing numerous basophilic granules and capable of releasing large amounts of histamine and heparin upon activation.

label.value: positive regulation of mast cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of mast cell differentiation, the process in which a relatively unspecialized myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a mast cell. A mast cell is a cell that is found in almost all tissues containing numerous basophilic granules and capable of releasing large amounts of histamine and heparin upon activation.

label.value: negative regulation of mast cell differentiation

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of mast cell differentiation, the process in which a relatively unspecialized myeloid precursor cell acquires the specialized features of a mast cell. A mast cell is a cell that is found in almost all tissues containing numerous basophilic granules and capable of releasing large amounts of histamine and heparin upon activation.
Any process that modulates brood size. Brood size is the number of progeny that survive embryogenesis and are cared for at one time.

The process in which a relatively unspecialized cell acquires specialized features of a cardiac myoblast. A cardiac myoblast is a precursor cell that has been committed to a cardiac muscle cell fate but retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life.

label.value: regulation of single-stranded telomeric DNA binding

value.value: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of binding to single-stranded telomeric DNA.

label.value: positive regulation of single-stranded telomeric DNA binding

value.value: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of single-stranded telomeric DNA binding.

Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of DNA strand elongation. DNA strand elongation is the DNA metabolic process in which an existing DNA strand is extended by activities including the addition of nucleotides to the 3' end of the strand.

label.value: positive regulation of DNA strand elongation

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of DNA strand elongation. DNA strand elongation is the DNA metabolic process in which an existing DNA strand is extended by activities including the addition of nucleotides to the 3' end of the strand.
The process in which a nerve invades a tissue and makes functional synaptic connection within the tissue.
The neurite development process that generates a long process of a neuron, as it invades a target tissue.
The assembly of a synapse within a target tissue in which a nerve is invading.
A structure that lies outside the plasma membrane and surrounds the egg. The fertilization envelope forms from the vitelline membrane after fertilization as a result of cortical granule release.
A glycoprotein-based structure that lies outside the plasma membrane and surrounds the egg before fertilization.

label.value: regulation of SMAD protein signal transduction

value.value: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of SMAD protein signal transduction.

label.value: positive regulation of SMAD protein signal transduction

value.value: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of SMAD protein signal transduction.

label.value: negative regulation of SMAD protein signal transduction

value.value: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of the SMAD protein signaling pathway.

An intracellular signaling cassette that starts with the activation of a SMAD protein, leading to the formation of a complex with co-SMADs, which translocates to the nucleus and regulates transcription of specific target genes.

definition.value: Note that the upstream receptor and its ligand regulate the pathway (and are not part of the SMAD pathway), since it is an intracellular signaling pathway.

value.value: The series of molecular signals generated as a consequence of growth hormone receptor binding to its physiological ligand.

label.value: growth hormone receptor signaling pathway via JAK-STAT

value.value: The process in which STAT proteins (Signal Transducers and Activators of Transcription) are activated by members of the JAK (janus activated kinase) family of tyrosine kinases, following the binding of physiological ligands to the growth hormone receptor. Once activated, STATs dimerize and translocate to the nucleus and modulate the expression of target genes.
